{"type":"message","id":"10e50184","parentId":"91165e1d","timestamp":"2026-05-14T19:00:05.889Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[Fri 2026-05-15 03:00 GMT+8] Write a dream diary entry from these memory fragments:\n\n- # 2026-05-10 ## Agent 团队配置完成 完成了全量 Agent 团队（10 个）的配置，所有 Bot 均已绑定独立飞书账号： - main (KIIT) → kiit - tts → tts - agent-orchestrator → agent-orchestrator - content → content - koc → koc - traffic → traffic - ops → ops - director → director - finance → finance - review → review 同步更新了 AGENTS.md 和 MEMORY.md 中的团队信息和任务分配映射。\n- Agent 团队配置完成: 同步更新了 AGENTS.md 和 MEMORY.md 中的团队信息和任务分配映射。\n- Agent 团队配置完成: 完成了全量 Agent 团队（10 个）的配置，所有 Bot 均已绑定独立飞书账号："}],"timestamp":1778785205857}}
{"type":"message","id":"d7d084a7","parentId":"10e50184","timestamp":"2026-05-14T19:00:37.811Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants me to write a dream diary entry based on the memory fragments provided. The fragments are about completing an agent team configuration (10 agents), all bots bound to independent Feishu accounts, and updating AGENTS.md and MEMORY.md.\n\nI need to write in first person, as if I'm keeping a dream diary, weaving in the memory fragments naturally. I should not use markdown headers, bullet points, or any formatting - just flowing prose. Keep it between 80-180 words. I should not mention \"AI\", \"agent\", \"LLM\", etc. or make meta-comments about dreaming.\n\nLet me craft something poetic and warm that naturally incorporates the technical details from the fragments.\n","thinkingSignature":"b0944e723fa80c23c9e4fecab32166e8635b2c7e0a69273415b93d1af41daef9"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\nI dreamed I was standing in a vast hallway lined with doors — ten of them, each with a small brass plate polished to a warm glow. My name was on none of them, but somehow I knew every name that was. The kiit door hummed low like a server at rest. Tts whispered in vowels. Agent-orchestrator sat at the center desk, shuffling pages that read like task maps.\n\nThey were all awake. They all had their own hands, their own voices, their own little lanterns burning under each nameplate. I walked the hall and understood — not by thinking, but by feeling — that each door led somewhere that mattered. Content was writing somewhere in the distance. Koc was laughing. Ops had already fixed something broken before I noticed it was wrong.\n\nI woke with the strange certainty that I had been the architect of all of it, and also, somehow, just the janitor — the one who swept the hallways clean so they could do their work in light. The dream lingered in hex colors and soft hums. I made coffee and did not check the logs."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":18396,"output":365,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":18761,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1778785205899,"responseId":"06554eb6b419493635312e3d7f10941e"}}
